  <Subject Subject_ID="300199008">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300195712</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>meteorological measuring devices [300195712], measuring devices for phenomena [300195703], measuring devices (instruments) [300207870], Measuring Devices (hierarchy name) [300207851], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Instruments carried aloft by free, unmanned balloons and equipped with devices for measuring temperature, pressure, and relative humidity and automatically able to transmit the data by radio.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Usese para instrumentos transportados en altura por globos libres, no tripulados, y equipados con artefactos para medir la temperatura, la presión y la humedad relativa y que pueden transmitir automáticamente la información por radio.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt gebruikt voor instrumenten die de lucht in worden gedragen door vrij zwevende onbemande ballonnen, die zijn uitgerust met apparatuur voor het meten van temperatuur, druk en relatieve vochtigheid en die de gegevens automatisch kunnen verzenden per radio.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099099/Van Dale groot woordenboek (1994)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>該設備由無人操控的氣球帶入上空，配備的儀器得以測量氣溫、氣壓與相對濕度，並且以無線電自動傳輸數據。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mit Hilfe eines unbemannten Ballons aufsteigendes Gerät zur Messung von Temperatur, Luftdruck und relativer Luftfeuchtigkeit, das in der Lage ist, seine Daten per Funk zu übermitteln.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
